### Motivation

In Avro schema definition, fields can be defined as either required or not. Typically this is automatically done when declaring a POJO in Java with nullable variables. Eg. 

```java
class Example {
   int a;
   Integer b;
}
```

In the above case, `a` is marked as required and `b` is optional. 

In Python declaration we need to have the same ability to declare fields as required, for interoperability with Java defined schemas.
